@storpipfugl: yes, and the docs should be more explicit about this

Sensors do take up a slot in your executor while they are running (sensing). You need to make sure you have plenty of slots available to support the max number of tasks that could ever run at the same time.

Sensors are typically cheap in terms of CPU / memory, so you can take that into account when factoring how many slots each worker should have.
